    <implementation-summary>
      Created Azure Dashboard and Alert Rules via Bicep for AI feature monitoring.

      1. Dashboard Module (infrastructure/bicep/modules/dashboard.bicep):
         - Row 1: Overview tiles (requests, success/failure, circuit breakers, tokens)
         - Row 2: RAG Performance (latency, throughput, breakdown)
         - Row 3: Tool Execution (executions, latency, token usage)
         - Row 4: Export Operations (requests, latency, file size)
         - Row 5: Resilience and Cache (circuit transitions, hit/miss, latency)

      2. Alert Rules Module (infrastructure/bicep/modules/alerts.bicep):
         - AI Failure Rate (dynamic threshold, critical)
         - Circuit Breaker Open (>0 open circuits, critical)
         - High RAG Latency (>3000ms avg, warning)
         - Tool Failures (dynamic threshold, warning)
         - Cache Miss Spike (dynamic threshold, warning)
         - High Token Usage (dynamic threshold, warning)
         - Export Failures (dynamic threshold, warning)

      3. Stack Integration (model2-full.bicep):
         - Added enableMonitoringDashboard parameter (default: true)
         - Added alertNotificationEmail parameter
         - Integrated dashboard and alerts modules

      4. Documentation (docs/guides/AI-MONITORING-DASHBOARD.md):
         - Dashboard panel descriptions
         - Alert rule reference
         - Access and sharing instructions
         - KQL queries for custom analysis
         - API endpoints for circuit breaker status
         - Troubleshooting guide

